é of François Truffaut, who honors him touchingly in his forword to Volume II. This new edition includes graceful forewords to each volume by Bazin scholar and biographer Dudley Andrew, who reconsiders Bazin and his place in contemporary film study. The essays themselves are erudite but always accessible, intellectual, and stimulating. As Renoir puts it, the essays of Bazin "will survive even if the cinema does not."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMotion pictures. 0aPerforming arts. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aauteur.  abazin.  acahiers du cinema.  achaplin.  acinema and screen.  acinema.  acitizen kane.  acritical theory.  acultural studies.  adigital film.  adirectors.  aediting.  aeroticism.  afellini.  afilm and animation.  afilm cinematography.  afilm criticism.  afilm genre.  afilm history.  afilm literature.  afilm movements.  afilm studies.  afilm technique.  afilm theory.  afilm.  afilmmaking.  afrench cinema.  aimage culture.  ajean renoir.  aliterary studies.  amass media.  amedia.  aneorealism.  anonfiction.  aorson welles.  aroberto rossellini.  asurrealism.  atruffaut.  avisual culture.1 aGray, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTruffaut, François, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024228940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093126840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520931268423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520931268/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyte